This paper deals with style transfer, which involves combining the content of one image with the artistic style of another. This is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to achieve style transfer, which is a popular technique in both computer graphics (cs.GR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for capturing style information from multiple images, which involves learning the optimal combination of style and content features. This is a task that could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
